  <steps>
    <step num="0">Heat the oil in a large pan over medium heat. Add the garlic and jalapeño and cook for about 2 minutes, until softened. </step>
    <step num="1">Add the black beans, corn, tomatoes, quinoa, vegetable stock, chili powder, cumin, salt, and pepper. Stir, then cover and cook for 15-20 minutes, until the liquid is absorbed and the quinoa is tender. </step>
    <step num="2">Transfer the salad to a serving bowl and top with the avocado, lime juice, and cilantro. </step>
    <step num="3">Enjoy! </step>
